HEADWORD: Self-assertion
<hw>Self`-as*ser"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of
asserting one's self, or one's own rights or claims; the quality of
being self-asserting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Self-assertive</ent>⟦br⟧
